**Greater Than (>) Comparison:**
The greater than operator is used to compare two values. It returns true if the value on the left is greater than the value on the right, and false otherwise.

**Syntax**
```cpp
if (value1 > value2) {
    // Code to execute if value1 is greater than value2
}
```
---

**Less Than (
using namespace std;

int main() {
    int num = 60;  // Set the input number directly here for testing

    // Check if the number is greater than 50
    if (num > 50) {
        cout << "The number is greater than 50." << endl;
    }

    // Check if the number is less than 50
    if (num < 50) {
        cout << "The number is less than 50." << endl;
    }
    return 0;
}
```

**Expected Output**
```default
The number is greater than 50.
```

